WINDOWS OS

Steps to Developing on a Client Computer :
-------------------------------------------
- Install Phpmystorm (http://www.jetbrains.com)
- Install msysgit (git program)

- Set PHPStorm Configs
    - add github username & pw (Settings > Githum)
    - add location of git.exe (Settings > Version Control > VCS > Git) [Last Known Location : C:\Program Files\Git\bin\git.exe]

- Open the GIT GUI
    - Help > Show SSH Key

    - $ cd ~/.ssh
    - $ ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "your_email@youremail.com" // should be your GitHub Email
    - On the GitHub site Click “Account Settings” > Click “SSH Public Keys” > Click “Add another public key”

- In PHP Storm,
    - Version Control > Checkout From GitHub


